A collection of general resources selected by Eric Hunting.

This is a companion page to the directory of [[Open Source Manufacturing Tools]]


=Articles=

Selection by Kevin Carson:

#[http://www.soilandhealth.org/03sov/0303critic/Brsdi.intrvw/The%20Plowboy-Borsodi%20Interview.htm Plowboy Interview]," Mother Earth News, March-April 1974: Ralph Borsodi discusses comparative efficiency of household vs. factory production
#Robert Williams, "[http://www.bcca.coop/pdfs/BolognaandEmilia.pdf Bologna and Emilia Romagna]:  A Model of Economic Democracy," paper presented to the annual meeting of the Canadian Economics Association, University of Calgary. May/June 2002.
#Jed, "[http://jed.jive.com/?p=23 Capitalists vs. Entrepreneurs]," Anomalous Presumptions, February 26, 2007. 
#Charles Johnson, "[http://radgeek.com/gt/2008/05/29/dump_the/ Dump the rentiers off your back]," Rad Geek People's Daily, May 29, 2008: Extremely valuable when read together with Jed.  On lower entry costs when many small units of capital can be aggregated with low transaction costs
#Jonathan Rowe, "[http://www.yesmagazine.org/article.asp?ID=1464 Entrepreneurs of Cooperation]," Yes!, Spring 2006: On direct production for barter during Depression


Also:

#Craig DeLancey, "Openshot," Analog, December 2006, pp. 64-74. Fictional depiction of open-source moon mission




=Books=

==Theory==

Books in with favourable arguments and material for distributing production, selected by Kevin Carson:

#Paul Hawken, Amory Lovins, and L. Hunter Lovins, [[Natural Capitalism]]:  Creating the Next Industrial Revolution (Boston, New
York, London:  Little, Brown and Company, 1999): Chapter on lean production relevant to networked local economies
#Michael H. Shuman, The [[Small-Mart Revolution]]:  How Local Businesses are Beating the Global Competition (San Francisco: Barrett-Koehler Publications, Inc., 2006, 2007).
#Colin Ward, Anarchy in Action (London:  Freedom Press, 1982): Material on community workshops
#Karl Hess, Community Technology (New York, Cambridge, Hagerstown, Philadelphia, San Francisco, London, Mexico City, Sao Paulo, Sydney: Harper & Row, Publishers, 1979), pp. 96-98. Material on community workshops
#Keith Paton, The Right to Work or the Fight to Live? (Stoke-on-Trent, 1972). Material on community workshops
#Ralph Borsodi, Flight From the City: On small-scale electrical machinery for household production
#Lewis Mumford, Technics and Civilization. Ditto, under heading of "neotechnic phase"


